<p>I'm trying to make a really simple title panel, which contains an <code>Image</code>-icon and <code>TextBlock</code>-title in the center of the panel:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/FM5Mp.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/FM5Mp.png" alt="enter image description here"></a> To achieve this with <code>TextBlock</code>, I could use <code>StackPanel</code> with <code>Vertical</code>-orientation. But this doesn't work when I need to add the <code>Image</code> in front of <code>TextBlock</code>.</p>  <p>This is the current code, which doesn't work with the <code>TextTrimming</code>:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal"&gt;     &lt;Image         Height="28"         Width="28"         Margin="0,0,10,0"         Source="/Resources/Images/Icons/MyIcon.png"         HorizontalAlignment="Left"         VerticalAlignment="Center"/&gt;      &lt;TextBlock x:Name="TitleText"         Text="Test text test text Test asd asd "         VerticalAlignment="Center"         FontSize="28"         TextWrapping="NoWrap"         TextTrimming="WordEllipsis"/&gt; &lt;/StackPanel&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Another solution could be to control the <code>Width</code> of the <code>TextBlock</code> in code, but I'd like to achieve this within <code>XAML</code>. Any ideas?</p>